{#
  home.njk — the overview / landing page (GET /).

  For this increment its job is to prove the boot worked: ingest ran (loads +
  operators) and the engine fanned out (detectors + surfaced findings), all from
  the in-memory read model with no database. The per-detector list, finding detail
  and live-threshold pages are added in their own plan items.
#}
{% extends "layout.njk" %}

{% from "govuk/components/summary-list/macro.njk" import govukSummaryList %}

{% block content %}
  <div class="govuk-grid-row">
    <div class="govuk-grid-column-two-thirds">
      <h1 class="govuk-heading-xl">Spot the Anomaly</h1>
      <p class="govuk-body-l">
        Anomaly detection over EPR packaging-waste export submissions, for a
        regulator to triage.
      </p>

      <h2 class="govuk-heading-m">This run</h2>
      {{ govukSummaryList({
        rows: [
          { key: { text: "Loads ingested" }, value: { text: summary.loads } },
          { key: { text: "Operator submissions" }, value: { text: summary.operators } },
          { key: { text: "Detectors run" }, value: { text: summary.detectors } },
          { key: { text: "Findings surfaced" }, value: { text: summary.findings } }
        ]
      }) }}

      <p class="govuk-body">
        These figures come from the fixtures ingested at boot and a single engine
        run held in memory — the demo runs database-free.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
{% endblock %}
